OOC: What's an Arcee.

BIC:  Mustex:  SIR YES SIR!

He escorted Nightshade to some quarters ,but stood
watch outside the door waiting for Hot Rod to return.

--- Jonathan <jhogan@...> wrote:
> 
> > Sunhawk picked up the transmission and smiled.
> >
> > Sunhawk:  Nevermind what I said SIR!  But I still
> want
> > to destroy that Predicon now.
> >
> > He continued waiting for an answer.
> >
> 
> {Talos}
> 
>     When Sunhawk had barged in Talos had looked up
> from what he was
> studying, in his hand was a small buckler sized
> chunk of metal, one side was
> detailed in pink and white with several faded
> splotches of red. Setting the
> object aside and turning to regard Sunhawk he
> sighed.
> 
>     "We will not be executing anyone Sunhawk. Not
> these predicons or any
> other. Our mission is to capture...not serve as
> judge jury and executioner.
> That's not our way, at least not mine. Escort Arc..I
> mean, Nightshade here
> to some quarters...and I do mean quarters not the
> brig Sunhawk, when Hot Rod
> returns from gathering the stasis pods he'll be
> assigned the duty of keeping
> an eye on her."
> 
>     Turning to pick up the peice of metal he looked
> down upon the insignia
> upon it, even the wear of time could not remove it
> completely and he had
> verified it's authenticity. Nightshade for all
> practical terms was what she
> had claimed to be. Maybe it was a mistake assigning
> Hot Rod to watch her,
> but he'd be able to tell if Nightshade was really
> the autobot Arcee or
> not...
> 
>     "Dismissed" He said simply, flipping the peice
> of metal back to it's
> owner.
> 
>     Nightshade smiled and caught the metal lifting
> her chest plate slightly
> and slipping it back into a compartment within as
> she stood and turned to
> Sunhawk, "We meet again and without you trying to
> kill me no less..."
> 
> 
>
